title: FOX23 Game of the Week: Broken Arrow at Jenks
text:
By Andrew Carter 
FOX23's Game of the Week features Broken Arrow at Jenks Friday night. 
It's a critical match-up with both district title implications and possible playoff positioning with Union on the line. 
Jenks has won the last three meetings and 10 of the last 11. 
The Trojans will host the Tigers in just their third home game of the season. Jenks head coach Allan Trimble talks about the match-up evaluates his team with playoffs around the corner. 
Jenks senior quarterback Cooper Nunley talks the big match-up. 
Jenks senior Dillon Stoner says the Trojans are ready for a hungry Tigers team. 
Broken Arrow head coach David Alexander talks about the importance of "Jenks week" and what it will take to win. 
Broken Arrow senior wide receiver Samuel Akem talks about how much this game means to the players. 
Broken Arrow senior Devon Johnson says Jenks is the Goliath but the Tigers won't back down. Sign up for our FOX23 News This Morning Newsletter Sign Up
